    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "fair enough. but if the structure is fundamentally broken like that, why do historians still treat the UN as the legitimate center of global governance? isn't there a valid argument that we should be looking at more nationalist or sovereign-led approaches instead of trying to fix a system that's clearly failing? it feels like the \"mainstream\" view just ignores that possibility.",
